title: 20th-century masterpieces on tap at fall NYC art auctions
text: > Entertainment 20th-century masterpieces on tap at fall NYC art auctions In this image provided by Christies is the painting, "Jeune homme a la fleur," by French artist Paul Gauguin. “Young Man with a Flower” depicts a Tahitian youth in a white shirt and loose cravat and a white blossom tucked behind his ear. Gauguin created it in 1891 soon after arriving on the French Polynesian island. It will be auctioned at Christie's, Nov. 9, 2015. (Christie's via AP)
